1
00:00:05,137 --> 00:00:06,387
What I find interesting,

2
00:00:06,387 --> 00:00:09,267
and found interesting 
since I was a teenager—

3
00:00:09,267 --> 00:00:11,706
it has been mentioned before—
growing up in New York,

4
00:00:11,706 --> 00:00:13,516
reading Bhagavad-gītā,

5
00:00:13,696 --> 00:00:15,956
[Renewing Truth]

6
00:00:16,086 --> 00:00:19,456
that the book itself deals

7
00:00:19,456 --> 00:00:29,272
with deviation, modification, 
adulteration of spiritual substance.

8
00:00:29,272 --> 00:00:35,355
I found that endearing
that this …

9
00:00:35,355 --> 00:00:38,547
In the 4th chapter of the Bhagavad-gītā
Kṛṣṇa’s saying, 
 

10
00:00:38,547 --> 00:00:44,197
“In time what was given, is lost.”
It degraded.

11
00:00:44,197 --> 00:00:47,197
In the 11th Canto 
of Śrīmad Bhāgavatam,

12
00:00:47,197 --> 00:00:49,937
what is Kṛṣṇa saying? 
His parting words to Uddhava,

13
00:00:49,937 --> 00:00:54,317
the śloka that mentions 
pāramparyeṇa prakṛti-vaicitryād 
[SB: 11.14.8]

14
00:00:54,317 --> 00:00:58,066
He said—prakṛti here means 
‘temperament’—

15
00:00:58,066 --> 00:01:02,370
He’s saying, “According 
to the temperament of the receiver

16
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:06,266
the truth,
it undergoes modification.”

17
00:01:06,553 --> 00:01:09,970
The famous example 
in classrooms—

18
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:14,130
teachers who were doing journalism 
or in other disciplines—

19
00:01:14,130 --> 00:01:16,389
there’s forty students, 
ten in each row;

20
00:01:16,389 --> 00:01:19,889
they tell the first person in a row,
they tell them something.

21
00:01:19,889 --> 00:01:22,248
And then they have to turn 
to the person next to him to tell them

22
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:27,958
all the way down the row, back up,
and then the last person stands up.

23
00:01:27,988 --> 00:01:30,713
And then the teacher would say,
“Right here’s the first person ...

24
00:01:30,713 --> 00:01:35,146
here’s what was said ...
and here’s the last person to receive it.”

25
00:01:35,146 --> 00:01:39,086
And then everyone starts laughing 
because in time

26
00:01:39,086 --> 00:01:43,676
with each telling it degraded, 
it became modified, adulterated,

27
00:01:43,676 --> 00:01:47,306
until it turned into something 
completely different.

28
00:01:47,306 --> 00:01:50,556
So Kṛṣṇa’s dealing with that 
in the Bhagavad-gītā. He is saying,

29
00:01:50,556 --> 00:01:55,485
“This happens! Factor this in!
Guaranteed, it will happen!”

30
00:01:55,485 --> 00:01:57,582
He’s not saying,
“Well, sometimes it happens,

31
00:01:57,582 --> 00:02:01,552
but it will never happen to us! 
We are so sincere.”

32
00:02:01,586 --> 00:02:04,636
No, He is not saying that. He is Kṛṣṇa.
He’s saying, “This happens”.

33
00:02:04,636 --> 00:02:07,287
This is the nature 
of the mundane world.

34
00:02:07,287 --> 00:02:10,557
There’s some Divine revelation, 
some Revealed Truth,

35
00:02:10,557 --> 00:02:12,510
there are receivers of that,

36
00:02:12,510 --> 00:02:16,600
and then according to the individual 
temperament it’s modified.

37
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:20,515
And then they pass it on to another, 
and you have a paramparā,

38
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:22,495
a line of descent.

39
00:02:22,495 --> 00:02:29,514
Now, just for the sake of argument, 
it’s also possible for it to become enhanced.

40
00:02:29,514 --> 00:02:33,469
As in the line of the Rūpānuga line, 
the Gosvāmīs,

41
00:02:33,469 --> 00:02:37,239
they are tasting that substance—
it’s becoming even more relishable.

42
00:02:37,239 --> 00:02:38,769
That’s also possible.

43
00:02:38,769 --> 00:02:45,729
But more possible and more likely 
is adulteration, modification, degradation.

44
00:02:45,729 --> 00:02:46,937
—Ok, here the question comes …

45
00:02:46,937 --> 00:02:48,070
—Wait to finish.

46
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:52,659
So Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says
in conclusion, in summary,

47
00:02:52,659 --> 00:02:59,725
“The truth is always inevitably,
invariably converted into error.”
 

48
00:02:59,975 --> 00:03:02,075
And we’ll say, “Oh …”

49
00:03:02,075 --> 00:03:11,515
The good news: he said, “Therefore 
living revelation, living realization

50
00:03:11,515 --> 00:03:19,082
will always be constantly necessary 
to restore the truth to its former purity.”

51
00:03:19,082 --> 00:03:22,699
So therefore it’s a job 
of each generation

52
00:03:22,699 --> 00:03:27,769
in a living way 
to realize Revealed Truth.

